	* ksrc/nucleus/pod.c (xnpod_shutdown): Drop nklock around
	xnheap_destroy invocations.

2008-09-08  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/nucleus/heap.c (xnheap_destroy_mapped): Handle last
	unmapping in heap deletion routine.

	* ksrc/native/{queue.c, heap.c}: Fix spurious -EBUSY upon
	deletion calls.

2008-09-03  Jan Kiszka  <jan.kiszka@web.de>

	* include/rtdm/rtdm.h: Align in-kernel socklen_t with spec, it
	contains only 32 valid bits.

	* ksrc/drivers/can/rtcan_socket.c (rtcan_socket_cleanup): Make
	rtcan_socket_list deregistration robust against reentrance.

2008-08-30  Gilles Chanteperdrix  <gilles.chanteperdrix@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/nucleus/shadow.c (gatekeeper_thread): Mask out
	TASK_ATOMICSWITCH test when testing hardening thread state, to
	take into account newer I-pipe patches with imporved ATOMICSWITCH
	support.

	* ksrc/nucleus/Kconfig: Select improved ATOMICSWITCH support if
	the I-pipe patch has it.

	* include/asm-arm/hal.h: Only use VFP if I-pipe patch has ironed
	VFP support.

	* include/asm-arm/syscall.h (__xn_rdtsc): Add an implementation of
	the tsc emulation for fast wrapping hardware timers.

	* configure.in: Select this tsc implementation for AT91.

2008-08-29  Jan Kiszka  <jan.kiszka@web.de>

	* src/rtdk/rt_print.c (rt_print_cleanup): Fix and improve cleanup,
	cancel printer thread.

2008-08-27  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/skins/vxworks/syscalls.c: Fix taskNametoId() wrapper, so
	that it returns the registry handle to userland, not the internal
	TCB address. Ensure taskInfoGet() returns the userland handle in
	TASK_DESC::td_tid.

2008-08-24  Gilles Chanteperdrix  <gilles.chanteperdrix@xenomai.org>

	* include/asm-arm/hal.h, configure.in: Add support for ARM MXC
	processors family.

	* include/asm-arm/bits/pod.h (xnarch_save/restore_fpu): Implement
	ARM VFP switching routines.

	* src/testsuite/switchtest/switchtest.c (check_fpu): Handle
	gracefully SIGILL by stopping using the FPU when switchtest is
	launched with no argument.

2008-08-22  Gilles Chanteperdrix  <gilles.chanteperdrix@xenomai.org>

	* configure.in: Add docdir if missing, in order to remain
	compatible with automake 1.9.

2008-08-22  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/nucleus/pipe.c: Fix handling of concurrent read/write sleep
	states on the same minor.
	
	* ksrc/nucleus/pipe.c (xnpipe_write): Fix inverted O_SYNC
	test. Block caller upon memory starvation; still honors
	O_NONBLOCK.

2008-08-19  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>
	
	* RELEASE: Xenomai 2.4.5 (Overdriver)

2008-08-19  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/nucleus/thread.c (xnthread_get_errno_location): Always
	return a pointer to in-TCB errno variable when running with
	CONFIG_XENO_OPT_PERVASIVE disabled.

	* ksrc/skins/posix/apc.c (pse51_lostage_handle_request): Exclude
	PSE51_LO_SIGNAL_REQ handling when CONFIG_XENO_OPT_PERVASIVE is
	disabled.

2008-08-18  Paul Corner <paul_c@tuxcnc.org>, Jan Kiszka <jan.kiszka@web.de>

	* ksrc/drivers/can/sja1000/rtcan_{isa, mem}.c: Add "can_" prefix
	to clock module parameter to avoid conflict with 2.6.26+ symbol.

2008-08-14  Jan Kiszka  <jan.kiszka@siemens.com>

	* include/nucleus/stat.h: Make xnstat_counter unsigned and extend
	it to long.

2008-08-13  Stephane Fillod  <stephane.fillod@thomson.net>

	* ksrc/arch/generic/hal.c: rthal_realtime_faults[][] should be
	unsigned to cope with (unexpectedly) large values.
	
2008-08-13  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/nucleus/shadow.c (request_syscall_restart): Notify about
	mode transition in the interrupted syscall case.

2008-08-12  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@eclipse.xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/nucleus/synch.c (xnsynch_sleep_on): Compute remaining
	timeout value using xntimer_get_timeout_stopped(), to resume timed
	wait on a stolen resource. This prevents early timeouts due to
	xnthread_timeout() always returning XN_INFINITE (0) for stopped
	timers.

2008-08-12  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* src/skins/native/{heap, queue}.c (rt_{heap, queue}_delete):
	Unmap the memory pool only after the actual deletion syscall
	returned successfully.

