	off-by-one reference error.

2008-06-18  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* thread.c (xnthread_get_errno_location): Allow operation on
	non-current threads.

	* ksrc/skins/vxworks/errnoLib.c (errnoOfTaskGet, errnoOfTaskSet):
	Refer to the target task's errno location (instead of current's).

	* ksrc/skins/vxworks/syscall.c (__wind_errno_taskset,
	__wind_errno_taskset): Allow calls from non-VxWorks tasks.


2008-06-08  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>
	
	* RELEASE: Xenomai 2.4.4 (Made Of Tears)

2008-06-08  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/arch/arm/patches: Upgrade to 2.6.25-arm-1.9-02.

	* ksrc/arch/blackfin/patches: Update to 2.6.22-blackfin-1.7-02.
	
	* ksrc/arch/powerpc/patches: Upgrade to 2.6.25-powerpc-2.2-02,
	2.6.20-powerpc-1.8-01.
	
	* ksrc/arch/x86/patches: Update to 2.6.25-x86-2.0-08.
	
2008-06-07  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/arch/powerpc/patches: Update to
	2.6.20-powerpc-1.8-00 (various fixes + legacy ppc/ support).

2008-06-05  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/arch/powerpc/patches: Upgrade to 2.6.24-powerpc-2.1-04,
	2.6.25-powerpc-2.2-00.

2008-06-04  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/nucleus/registry.c: Allocate registry_obj_slots[]
	dynamically to work around limited data mapping during early boot
	on ppc (same issue that required CONFIG_IPIPE_TRACE_VMALLOC to be
	provided).

2008-06-03  Gilles Chanteperdrix  <gilles.chanteperdrix@xenomai.org>

	* src/skins/posix/mutex.c (__wrap_pthread_mutex_trylock, 
	__wrap_pthread_mutex_unlock): trap the -EINTR return value.

2008-06-02  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* include/asm-powerpc/calibration.h: Add calibration value for
	the MPC8349_ITX board.

	* ksrc/arch/blackfin/patches: Update to 2.6.22-blackfin-1.7-01.

2008-06-01  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/nucleus/shadow.c (xnshadow_map): Do not set the underlying
	Linux task priority; this is useless since userland is expected to
	set it properly before attempting a shadow mapping, and also
	contradicts the cached priority value maintained by the glibc.

	* ksrc/nucleus/shadow.c (do_setsched_event): Do not propagate
	 priority changes to the nucleus for threads that belong to skins
	 that have a priority scale not compatible with the POSIX one.

2008-05-31  Gilles Chanteperdrix  <gilles.chanteperdrix@xenomai.org>

	* configure.in (--enable-arm-mach): Add a "generic" machine.
	(--disable-arm-tsc): Enable ARM tsc emulation by default.

2008-05-27  Gilles Chanteperdrix  <gilles.chanteperdrix@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/skins/posix/signal.c (pse51_sigqueue_inner): Fix posix
	shadows signals: only trigger xnshadow_relax if the target thread
	is not already suspended from the nucleus point of view.

2008-05-27  Sebastian Smolorz  <sesmo@gmx.net>

	* ksrc/skins/native/pipe.c (rt_pipe_receive): Fix documentation
	for the return values of the function. -EIDRM is no valid return
	value any more.

2008-05-25  Gilles Chanteperdrix  <gilles.chanteperdrix@xenomai.org>

	* include/nucleus/intr.h, include/nucleus/thread.h: Fix
	compilation of posix applications in user-space with ucLibc.

2008-05-25  Roland Stigge  <stigge@antcom.de>

	* doc/man/*: Add new manual pages.

2008-05-25  Wolfgang Grandegger  <wg@grandegger.com>

	* ksrc/drivers/can/mscan/rtcan_mscan.c (rtcan_mscan_exit): Fix
	section mismatch warning.

2008-05-25  Wolfgang Grandegger  <wg@grandegger.com>

	* ksrc/drivers/can/mscan/rtcan_mscan.c: Remove #include <ppcboot.h>
	because it's not needed at all and it makes trouble with kernel
	version >= 2.6.24.

2008-05-24  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/skins/vxworks/syscall.c (__wind_msgq_receive): Fix byte
	count for copy to user.

2008-05-22  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/arch/powerpc/patches: Update to 2.6.24-powerpc-2.1-03.

	* ksrc/arch/x86/patches: Update to 2.6.24-x86-2.0-07,
	2.6.25-x86-2.0-07.

	* src/skins/{native,vxworks}/wrappers.[ch]: Define a wrapper file
	maintaining a list of placeholders for routines that we do NOT
	want to be wrapped to their Xenomai POSIX API counterparts when
	linked with our POSIX library, and use those symbols throughout
	the interfaces.

2008-05-22  Yi Li <liyi.dev@gmail.com>

	* ksrc/arch/blackfin/patches: Resync patch on 2008R1. Add support
	for bf54x and bf52x.

2008-05-20  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/arch/x86/patches: Upgrade to 2.6.25-x86-2.0-06.

2008-05-19  Jan Kiszka  <jan.kiszka@web.de>

	* include/asm-x86/bits/shadow_64.h (xnarch_init_shadow_tcb): Keep
	pointing at register "rip" within the thread struct.

2008-05-17  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/skins/native/task.c (rt_task_send): Apply infinite timeout
	to wait for a reply once a remote server has been found, in the
	non-blocking call case. NOTE: Passing TM_NONBLOCK does NOT mean
	not to wait for a reply, but it means to wait for a reply UNLESS
	no server is listening to us before we send the request.

	* ksrc/nucleus/shadow.c (rpi_update): Handle calls for non
	RPI-boosted threads gracefully; those are legit.

2008-05-15  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* src/skins/vxworks, ksrc/skins/vxworks: Add taskInfoGet()
	service.

	* ksrc/nucleus/synch.c (xnsynch_sleep_on): Check last wchan
	signaled to prevent a race on interpreting the XNWAKEN flag. The
	actual case that patch fixes is as follows:
	- Thread A grabs synch X
	- Thread A sleeps on synch Y
	- Synch Y is signaled, thread A is unblocked but not immediately
	resumed CPU-wise, XNWAKEN is raised.
	- Thread B mistakenly steals synch X, being confused by the
	XNWAKEN state of thread A, but which is applicable to a different
	synch object (synch Y).

	To fix this, we need to make sure that XNWAKEN applies to the
	ownership of the right synchronization object -- this is the
	purpose of the new thread->wwake field. Another option would be to
	have the synchronization object hold the steal state, but this
	would raise other issues.

2008-05-15  Gernot Hillier  <gernot.hillier@siemens.com>

	* configure.in: Disallow includedir == /usr/include.

2008-05-15  Markus Osterried <markus.osterried@ericsson.com>

	* src/skins/psos/tm.c (tm_evevery): Fix system call number.

2008-05-13  Jan Kiszka  <jan.kiszka@siemens.com>

	* ksrc/nucleus/pod.c (xnpod_delete_thread): Invoke xnfreesync
	if executed over the root thread to avoid potentially long
	pending TCB releases until next root switch-in.

2008-05-12  Jan Kiszka  <jan.kiszka@web.de>

	* ksrc/arch/x86/smi.c, ksrc/drivers/can/sja1000/rtcan_peak_dng.c:
	Fix section violations by removing some __devinit and __exit
	annotations.

2008-05-11  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* include/asm-x86: Adapt to 2.6.25.

2008-05-07  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/skins/vxworks/semLib.c: Rework mutex support.

2008-05-09  Jan Kiszka  <jan.kiszka@siemens.com>

	* ksrc/nucleus/shadow.c (do_taskexit_event): Unlock timers when
	debugged thread exits.

2008-05-06  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/nucleus/shadow.c (do_schedule_event): Do not grab the
	sighand lock for reading the signal pending mask: it's useless,
	and exposes us to deadlocks on SMP because we own the runqueue
	lock here.

2008-05-06  Klaas Gadeyne <klaas.gadeyne@fmtc.be>

	* ksrc/skins/native/cond.c (rt_cond_wait): Fix
	documentation (ETIMEDOUT status).
	
2008-05-03  Gilles Chanteperdrix  <gilles.chanteperdrix@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/skins/posix/mutex.h (pse51_mutex_timedlock_internal):
	Correctly restore the mutex recursion count after suspension in
	a condition variable.

2008-05-02  Jan Kiszka  <jan.kiszka@siemens.com>

	* ksrc/skins/posix/syscall.c: Fix pthread_cond/mutex_init for NULL
	attributes, remove questionable locking around sem/mutex/cond
	initialization and destruction (backport of #3369).

2008-04-25  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

	* ksrc/skins/vxworks/semLib.c: (sem_create_internal): Clear the
	owner field at init.

2008-04-25  Philippe Gerum  <rpm@xenomai.org>

